## Is Something Technical Blocking Your Rankings?

Rankings that plateau without explanation, pages that should rank but don't, traffic that drops after a Google update: these are almost always technical problems. The challenge is that technical SEO issues are invisible to website owners. They don't show as error messages, and they don't stop the site working. They simply prevent pages from reaching their ranking potential.

Most websites have between 15 and 40 technical issues. A handful, such as crawl blocks, canonicalisation errors, and Core Web Vitals failures, actively suppress rankings regardless of content quality or backlinks. A technical SEO audit identifies exactly which issues are holding your site back, ranked by impact so your development team focuses on the changes that actually move the needle.

**Initial consultations are free.** Book a call, get an immediate assessment of your site's biggest technical issues, and decide whether a full audit makes sense, no commitment required.

