## How to Choose an SEO Audit Service in the UK

UK businesses buying SEO audit services choose between automated tools, independent consultants, and agencies. The pricing tiers above cover the cost differences; the practical difference is who does the work and what you can act on afterwards. Ask any provider four questions before committing:

1. **Who performs the audit?** With an independent consultant, the person selling the audit is the person doing it. Agencies often delegate audits to junior staff working from templates.
2. **Is every finding manually verified?** Automated crawls flag false positives. A finding is only worth developer time if a human has confirmed it affects your site.
3. **Does the report prioritise by effort and impact?** A list of 200 unranked issues is a tool export, not an audit. You need to know which 15 fixes move rankings.
4. **Is a walkthrough call included?** A PDF without a conversation leaves your team guessing. Every audit here includes a 60-minute findings call.

If you need content quality and AI-search visibility assessed alongside the technical layer, the [fixed-fee £495 SEO audit](/services/paid-seo-audit/) covers all three in one engagement, with the fee credited against your first month if we go on to work together.

